# time-series-exploration ‚Äî project context

Streaming time-series forecasting demo with drift detection, retraining,
and MLflow 3 tracking. Synthetic grid-load data, GradientBoostingRegressor,
file-based MLflow store. Local dev only.

## Run it

- `make mlflow-server` ‚Äî MLflow UI at `http://localhost:5001`
  (host=127.0.0.1, backend=`./mlruns`, artifact root=`./mlartifacts`)
- `make streaming` / `python run_streaming.py` ‚Äî in-process synthetic
  stream, retrains on drift, registers best model at the end.
- Kafka path (branch `feature/kafka-streaming`, requires `uv sync --extra kafka`):
  - `make kafka-workflow` ‚Äî prints the multi-terminal demo steps
  - `make mlflow-server` + `make kafka-up` ‚Äî start both before producer/consumer
  - `make check-deps` ‚Äî preflight (MLflow `:5001` + Kafka `:19092`)
  - `make kafka-producer` / `make streaming-kafka` ‚Äî fail fast if deps are down
  - `make kafka-monitor` ‚Äî second consumer group (learning exercise)
  - With uv: `make streaming-kafka PYTHON="uv run --extra kafka python"`
  - See `docs/kafka-learning.md` for replay/resume exercises.
- Ctrl+C is graceful (two-stage SIGINT). Run gets status=KILLED, no register.

## MLflow store layout

- `mlruns/` = backend (metadata, metric files, params, tags).
- `mlartifacts/` = artifact store (model packages, parquet features).
- Both are gitignored. Local archive of pre-fix bloated runs lives in
  `mlruns_archive_bloated/` + `mlartifacts_archive_bloated/`.
- Active experiment id `906404254415785531` = `TimeSeries-Development`.

## Streaming-cost landmines (do NOT regress)

- `ForecastPipeline.buffer` is `collections.deque(maxlen=BUFFER_SIZE)`.
  Never make it an unbounded list ‚Äî training cost has to stay flat.
- Do NOT call `mlflow.sklearn.log_model(name=...)` per retrain. MLflow 3
  runs `log_model_metrics_for_step` inside `log_model`, which fetches and
  re-attaches the run's full metric history every call ‚Üí O(N¬≤) ‚Üí 25s+
  per retrain by v19. We use `mlflow.sklearn.save_model` to a temp dir
  then `mlflow.log_artifacts(...)`.
- Always pass `pip_requirements=[...]` explicitly. Default (`None`) spawns
  a per-call subprocess for env introspection (~1.3s baseline, grows
  with parent-process memory).
- `create_features` writes parquet locally only. The pipeline runner
  uploads `storage/features/features.parquet` once in its `finally`
  block. Do not log it per retrain.

## Key files

- `pipeline/forecasting_pipeline.py` ‚Äî loop, drift, graceful shutdown.
- `models/training.py` ‚Äî train + save_model + log_artifacts.
- `models/registry.py` ‚Äî best-model registration. Known follow-up: the
